<title>GERMANY: German SAP raises dividend, pays bonus.</title>
<headline>German SAP raises dividend, pays bonus.</headline>
<dateline>WALLDORF, Germany 1997-03-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>German business software group SAP AG said on Wednesday it would raise the dividend for its shares for 1996 results and pay an additional bonus to mark its 25th anniversary.</p>
<p>The dividend on ordinary stock will rise to 1.80 marks from 1.30 marks, while dividends on preference shares will rise to 1.85 marks from 1.35 marks.</p>
<p>In addition, the company will pay a bonus of 50 pfennigs per share.</p>
<p>The company repeated that net profit in 1996 rose 40 percent to 568 million marks and sales surged 38 percent to 3.7 billion marks.</p>
<p>-- Bonn Newsroom, 49 228 26097150</p>
